70 Project Description: We are seeking a skilled and experienced Three.js and Ammo.js developer to create a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) for a virtual try-on experience within a 1-month timeframe. Project Goal: The goal of our project is to develop a functional MVP where users can visualize how garments fit on a static 3D avatar using realistic cloth physics. This MVP will serve as a proof of concept to validate the feasibility of a virtual try-on experience. In more detail: users can create a 3d avatar by uploading a picture (solution already developed), then we work with brands to create 3d replicas of clothes (solution already developed). The clothes now need to be displayed realistically on 3d avatars in the web, without clipping, and natural stretch - cloth physics. !! You will only work on developping the system (using three.js, ammo.js or other) to display clothes on the 3d avatar with physics simulation. !! Technical Requirements Approach (Recommended but Open to Alternatives): We envision a solution leveraging the power of Three.js for rendering and Ammo.js for physics simulations. We are particularly interested in an approach that incorporates: - Physics World Setup (Ammo.js): Creation of a physics environment with gravity and collision detection. - Avatar as Rigid Body: Implementation of the 3D avatar as a rigid body within the physics world. - Garment as Soft Body (Cloth): Development of the garment as a soft body (cloth) using Ammo.js, allowing for realistic draping and deformation. - Garment Pinning/Constraints: Implementation of methods to pin or constrain the garment to the avatar at specific points (e.g., shoulders, waist, seams) to simulate garment attachment and fit. - Three.js Rendering: Utilizing Three.js for efficient and visually appealing rendering of the avatar and garment. - Basic User Interaction: Implementation of camera controls (orbit controls) to allow users to rotate and zoom the view. Important Notes: - Static Avatar: For this MVP, the avatar will be static (not animated). - Timeline: 1 Month: The project needs to be completed within approximately one month. - Open to Alternative Approaches: While the above approach is our preferred direction, we are open to alternative technical solutions that can effectively achieve the project goal within the timeframe. Please propose your approach in your application if you have a different strategy in mind. 75 We consider only Android Native Development. Fishing Forecast App - designed to help anglers plan the most successful day, time, and location for fishing, the app utilizes data from various sources (meteorological, hydrological, and astronomical) to provide a fishing conditions forecast. The Application Has Three Main Sections: Forecast – This is the default section where users receive a fish activity forecast for 8 to 15 days ahead. Calendar—This section allows users to access the Solunar forecast. It does not consider many factors but allows users to get a forecast for up to a year ahead. Settings – Application settings. Application Workflow 1. The user selects a location on the map / enters an address/coordinates/place name. 2. The app requests several APIs (weather, astronomical) and saves answers for further processing 3. The system calculates scores for all factors (score logic will be provided), sums them up, and generates an overall fishing score. Example scoring: - Pressure in the range of 1010-1020 hPa, with no changes greater than ≤1 hPa per day = 2 points - Solunar forecast (Moon illumination) from 0% to 3% = 2 points - Partly cloudy (11% - 79%) = 0.5 points - Moderate wind (4–7 m/s) = 0.5 points - Fishing Score = 5 4. The subscription screen is displayed (optional) 5. The fishing forecast is displayed on the screen (some content may be hidden if the user has not subscribed). Remote Config The project requires flexible management of subscriptions, subscription screen displays, hidden content, and fishing forecast settings using Firebase Remote Config. Additionally, it must support A/B testing for different configuration options. Implementation Using Firebase Remote Config: - Subscription Availability - Close Button on the Subscription Screen - Subscription Design - Ability to change pricing, design, and text for different subscription screen displays (1st display - 8.99; 2nd display - 3.99; 3rd display - 1.99) - Design Variants - Hidden Content for Non-Subscribers Subscription Display Triggers: - When requesting a fishing forecast - When clicking on a specific UI element Additional Features: - Ability to change forecast evaluation scoring dynamically - Privacy Policy / Terms of Use Popup - A/B Testing support for different configurations Push notifications - Push notifications need to be implemented, as they are required for one of the subscription plans. 77 We consider only iOS Native Development. Fishing Forecast App - designed to help anglers plan the most successful day, time, and location for fishing, the app utilizes data from various sources (meteorological, hydrological, and astronomical) to provide a fishing conditions forecast. The Application Has Three Main Sections: Forecast – This is the default section where users receive a fish activity forecast for 8 to 15 days ahead. Calendar—This section allows users to access the Solunar forecast. It does not consider many factors but allows users to get a forecast for up to a year ahead. Settings – Application settings. Application Workflow 1. The user selects a location on the map / enters an address/coordinates/place name. 2. The app requests several APIs (weather, astronomical) and saves answers for further processing 3. The system calculates scores for all factors (score logic will be provided), sums them up, and generates an overall fishing score. Example scoring: - Pressure in the range of 1010-1020 hPa, with no changes greater than ≤1 hPa per day = 2 points - Solunar forecast (Moon illumination) from 0% to 3% = 2 points - Partly cloudy (11% - 79%) = 0.5 points - Moderate wind (4–7 m/s) = 0.5 points - Fishing Score = 5 4. The subscription screen is displayed (optional) 5. The fishing forecast is displayed on the screen (some content may be hidden if the user has not subscribed). Remote Config The project requires flexible management of subscriptions, subscription screen displays, hidden content, and fishing forecast settings using Firebase Remote Config. Additionally, it must support A/B testing for different configuration options. Implementation Using Firebase Remote Config: - Subscription Availability - Close Button on the Subscription Screen - Subscription Design - Ability to change pricing, design, and text for different subscription screen displays (1st display - 8.99; 2nd display - 3.99; 3rd display - 1.99) - Design Variants - Hidden Content for Non-Subscribers Subscription Display Triggers: - When requesting a fishing forecast - When clicking on a specific UI element Additional Features: - Ability to change forecast evaluation scoring dynamically - Privacy Policy / Terms of Use Popup - A/B Testing support for different configurations Push notifications - Push notifications need to be implemented, as they are required for one of the subscription plans. SDK to install : - AppsFlyer - Firebase (Crashlytics, Google Analytics, AB testing, Remote config) - Facebook SDK - Amplitude - RevenueCat Localization - EN - Other (up to 5) Design - https://www.figma.com/design/PbejOBXl92JXTGcNtcZ3oq/Fishing-forecast-draft-2.0?node-id=0-1 t=HjuybhoLbpREDebZ-1 Prototype (it’s not the full version, just for a quick view) - https://www.figma.com/proto/PbejOBXl92JXTGcNtcZ3oq/Fishing-forecast-draft-2.0?node-id=0-763 p=f t=zd6Wz2oxlyqggLhD-1 scaling=min-zoom content-scaling=fixed page-id=0%3A1 starting-point-node-id=0%3A763 In your proposal please include: - Estimated price for the entire project, at least range - Estimated time required to complete the project, at least range - Estimated number of working hours needed, at least range null<nullexplain>The provided text does not contain any URLs that could lead to the employer's contact information, portfolio, or personal website. 79 Native Android Kotlin App Code Google Play - Update rejected - All Files Access Permission policy: Need to use MediaStore API Status You requested access to All files access permission but it appears that your app's core feature requires access to only Media Files or doesn't need access to any files. In either case, you need to remove All files access permission since access to all files isn’t critical to your app’s core functionality. If users needs access and store Media Files only, you should use the MediaStore API. This API permits your app to contribute to and access media that’s available on an external storage volume without the need for the All files access permission. Update your app so that the feature uses MediaStore APIs and remove All files access (MANAGE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE) permission.
